cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a new development of Reiter's temporal situation calculus action theories, which is directly inspired by hybrid systems in control theory. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with modeling continuous change. It also involves logical reasoning, which suggests it could be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses regression and reasoning problems, which could place it under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
